1️⃣ GOVERNANCE & DECISION SYSTEMS

(Authority, not compliance)

What this is

A formal decision framework that defines who can change the platform, under what conditions, and with what accountability.

How it works
	•	Decision authority model
	•	AI behavior → AI Lead / Founder
	•	Content & tone → Editorial authority
	•	Commerce & vendors → Commerce authority
	•	Dual-approval rules
	•	Any change affecting legality, safety, or monetization requires two roles
	•	Emergency override
	•	One designated role can freeze features instantly
	•	Decision logs
	•	Every material change records:
	•	What changed
	•	Why
	•	Who approved
	•	When it takes effect
	•	Separation of duties
	•	No single role controls AI + content + commerce

Why it matters

Without this, power concentrates, mistakes compound, and trust erodes internally before users ever notice.

⸻

2️⃣ OPERATIONAL CADENCE & PLATFORM HYGIENE

(Rhythm keeps systems honest)

What this is

A recurring operational heartbeat that ensures nothing quietly rots.

How it works
	•	Weekly
	•	Trust & safety spot checks
	•	AI output sampling
	•	Monthly
	•	Vendor review
	•	Affiliate link audit
	•	Legal language scan
	•	Quarterly
	•	Content pruning
	•	Feature relevance review
	•	Guardrail drift assessment

